Deep within the bowls of Cybertron, a crypt of Decepticons lay untouched for 
many years. Silent... dark... all there were by no means functioning. 

Yet in the darkness, 2 glowing eyes appeared as they moved like 2 tiny ghosts 
through the darkness of the crypt. They approached the center, the heart of 
the crypt, a soft glowing light in rememberance of those brave Decepticons 
who ceased to function in battle.

As the 2 glowing lights soon enough revealed they belonged to a form that did 
function!

A beast machine, in the form of an Earth white bengal tiger stood in the 
light, basking in it&#39;s soft glow. The optics of this regal creature glanced 
about as it seemed to realize where it was, & understand the nightmare it was 
in. The optics soon enough looked at it&#39;s current form.. to it&#39;s horror! 

RrrAAARRRRRRRROOOWWWWWLLLLLLLLUUUNNNGGHHHHHHAAAAAAA!!!!! as the blood curling 
cry went out, echoing throughout the crypt.

The creature found it extremely hard to transform, unable to at this time. 
What was once familiar to her, was no more. This new form was by no means 
welcome.

She walked over between the statues of Thundercracker & Skywarp, her friends &
 fellow comrades during the Great War. As she laid down at their feet, they 
were now large than her, she hated this already. A soft howl, moan & whimper 
came from her. Emotions? This was unusual. She was a Decepticon, not some.. 
organic creature. But she was not totally organic. This confused her more.

In a broken, uneasy deep feminine feline. &quot;What... is.. happening.. to .. 
me?!&quot; she growled as she laid at the feet of the Decepticon statues.


